# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Date: 11-03-2026

## Status

🤔 Proposed

## Context

For practicality purposes we currently allow various write level permissions on our management account as well as access to various management secrets.

As all developers have access to the operator role this poses an increased security risk of mistake or malicious activity against management.

Some examples of possible issues could include exfiltration of secrets, modification of dns records or modification of ECR images so that the live service runs a malicious image.

## Decisions

The suggestion is to

- Downgrade operator role in the management account to be read only except for s3 where it needs further permissions currently for state writes (that we can modify at a future date)
- Provide service level roles in management which we could use in our terraform instead of breakglass when we would otherwise be modifying resources in management.
- Update terraform service providers and/or envrc files to use the new role instead of breakglass for management provider

The suggested name for the new role would be: {service_name}-operations
The suggested trusted user for the role would be: WebOps

We could set up separate team based groups if we felt that were needed.

## Consequences

- Could make the operator role less impactful if it were compromised.
- Developers would have to use CI pipeline to spin up their development environments. However, they could still modify non management resources using terraform.
- WebOps would be able to carry out large bits of infrastructure work from the cli still without needing to trigger breakglass alarms.
